title: The week in numbers to Oct 16
text:
Fri, Oct 16, 2015, 12:48 PM AEDT - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 12 mins The week in numbers to Oct 16 AAP – 1 hour 40 minutes ago Recommend 
The big and small numbers that grabbed attention - or should have - in the business world over the past week. 
Monday: 
$4.25m - Bernie Brookes earned $4.25 million in his final year as the boss of Myer despite a failed merger bid and a nearly 70 per cent decline in net profit. 
Tuesday: 
$80m - Telstra estimates the competition watchdog's ruling that it must cut what it charges other telcos to access the Telstra copper wire network will cost $80 million. That's $80 million telcos such as Optus and iiNet can pass on to their customers because they won't be paying it to Telstra. 
Wednesday: 
0.2 pct - Westpac is passing on some of the cost of new capital requirements to home loan customers, hiking variable mortgage rates by 0.2 percentage points. Its rivals are expected to follow, and experts think that will increase the chances of an RBA rate cut. 
Thursday: 
5,100 - Unemployment was steady at 6.2 per cent in September, but the number of people with jobs fell by 5,100 in the month, worse than economists' expectations of a 5,000 gain. 
Friday: 
8.5m - Volkswagen will recall 8.5 million diesel vehicles Europe-wide, as police raided the carmaker's office in Italy and those of its Lamborghini business over the global pollution-cheating scandal. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Rio Tinto boosts quarterly shipments AAP
